Definition: a Marxist terrorist group formed in 1963 by Colombian intellectuals who were inspired by the Cuban Revolution
Example: responsible for a campaign of mass kidnappings and resistance to the government's efforts to stop the drug trade; ELN kidnappers target foreign employees of large corporations
Synonyms: ELN, terrorist_organization, i, noun, act, terrorism, c, location, Colombia, r, a, Marxist, terrorist, group, formed, in, by, Colombian, intellectuals, who, were, inspired, the, Cuban, Revolution, responsible, for, campaign, of, mass, kidnappings, and, resistance, to, government, s, efforts, stop, drug, trade, kidnappers, target, foreign, employees, large, corporations
Category: noun.group
